    "updated_at": "2016-06-17T22:33:59Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Closing as per [upstream issue](https://github.com/jonathanslenders/python-prompt-toolkit/issues/265):\n\n> We can't do this by default. Handling escape in reverse search would mean that Alt-Enter doesn't won't work anymore. (Alt-enter in reverse search should execute the current match right away.)\n> It's more important to have alt-enter work than to have Esc as an alias for Control-G and Control-C.\n"
